-avoid_node_id

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

The IPv4 address identifying the immediate downstream node that the PLR is trying to avoid. The Router ID of the downstream node is the preferred value.

DEFAULT

-count

Supported platforms Details

DESCRIPTION

DEFAULT

-egress_ip_addr

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

IP address of the tunnel's egress point.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.This parameter exists in the implementation of RSVP-TE P2P but it has a new meaning in the implementation for P2MP. Parameters count, egress_ip, egress_ip_step, egress_leaf_range_count, egress_leaf_range_step, egress_leaf_ip_count configure how P2MP tunnel leaves are configured. The -count parameter configures the number of Egress P2MP tunnel tails.The -egress_ip parameter configures the IPv4 address of the first P2MP tunnel leaf of the first Egress P2MP Tunnel tail. The parameter -egress_ip_step configures the step which will increment the IPv4 address of the -egress_ip_addr when there are multiple Egress P2MP Tunnel Tails configured.The -egress_leaf_range_count parameter configures how many P2MP leaf ranges are configured per Egress P2MP Tunnel Tail.The -egress_leaf_range_step configures the IPv4 step used to increment egress_ip_addr when there are multiple leaf_ranges configured.The -egress_leaf_ip_count parameter configures how many P2MP leaves will be configured in an egress P2MP tunnel leaf range.Example: -count 3egress_ip_addr 5.5.5.5egress_ip_addr_step 1.0.0.0egress_leaf_range_count 3egress_leaf_range_step 0.1.0.0egress_leaf_ip_count 15Configuration Result:Egress1Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 5.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 5.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 5.7.5.5Leaf Count 15Egress 2Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 6.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 6.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 6.7.5.5Leaf Count 15Egress 3Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 7.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 7.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 7.7.5.5Leaf Count 15(DEFAULT = N/A)Dependencies: N/A.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

This value is used to increment egress IP address when configuring multiple tunnels.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

The -count parameter configures the number of Egress P2MP tunnel tails.The -egress_ip parameter configures the IPv4 address of the first P2MP tunnel leaf of the first Egress P2MP Tunnel tail. The parameter -egress_ip_step configures the step which will increment the IPv4 address of the -egress_ip_addr when there are multiple Egress P2MP Tunnel Tails configured.The -egress_leaf_range_count parameter configures how many P2MP leaf ranges are configured per Egress P2MP Tunnel Tail.The -egress_leaf_range_step configures the IPv4 step used to increment egress_ip_addr when there are multiple leaf_ranges configured.The -egress_leaf_ip_count parameter configures how many P2MP leaves will be configured in an egress P2MP tunnel leaf range.Example: -count 3egress_ip_addr 5.5.5.5egress_ip_addr_step 1.0.0.0egress_leaf_range_count 3egress_leaf_range_step 0.1.0.0egress_leaf_ip_count 15Configuration Result:Egress1Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 5.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 5.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 5.7.5.5Leaf Count 15Egress 2Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 6.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 6.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 6.7.5.5Leaf Count 15Egress 3Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 7.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 7.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 7.7.5.5Leaf Count 15Dependencies: N/A.

-h2l_info_ero_sero_list

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.This parameter configures a list of ero/sero objects on a Tunnel Head To Leaf Information object. ERO/SERO objects can be configured as either IP or AS. The following format must be used for IP type: ip,,ip = the 'ip' keywordipv4_address -- an IPv4 addressprefix -- the prefix length for the ip address (range 1-32)'l' - corresponding L bit in the packet will be set's' - corresponding L bit in the packet will not be setFor 'as' type the accepted format is as,, as -- 'as' keyword - number of the AS'l' - corresponding L bit in the packet will be set's' - corresponding L bit in the packet will not be setIn this way one ERO/SERO object is configured on all the Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects. You can configure multiple ERO/SERO objects on all the Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects by separating the format mentioned above with the ":" character.Example: "ip,1.0.1.0/32,s:ip,0.0.1.0/32,l"To configure a separate ERO/SERO object list on each Tunnel Head To Leaf you can pass this parameter on as a list.Example: count 2 h2l_info_tunnel_leaf_prefix_length [list 16 24]h2l_info_ero_sero_list [list ip,1.0.1.0/32,s:as,13,l ip,15.15.15.15/24,s:as,14,s] This will configure two P2MP tunnels. Each tunnel will have two Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects. The first Head To Leaf Info object will have two ERO/SERO objects (ip 1010 and as 13), the second will also have two ERO/SERO objects (ip 15.15.15.15 and as 14).

 None

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.This parameter exists in the implementation of RSVP-TE P2P but it has a new meaning in the implementation for P2MP. Parameters count, egress_ip, egress_ip_step, egress_leaf_range_count, egress_leaf_range_step, egress_leaf_ip_count configure how P2MP tunnel leaves are configured. The -count parameter configures the number of Egress P2MP tunnel tails.The -egress_ip parameter configures the IPv4 address of the first P2MP tunnel leaf of the first Egress P2MP Tunnel tail. The parameter -egress_ip_step configures the step which will increment the IPv4 address of the -egress_ip_addr when there are multiple Egress P2MP Tunnel Tails configured.The -egress_leaf_range_count parameter configures how many P2MP leaf ranges are configured per Egress P2MP Tunnel Tail.The -egress_leaf_range_step configures the IPv4 step used to increment egress_ip_addr when there are multiple leaf_ranges configured.The -egress_leaf_ip_count parameter configures how many P2MP leaves will be configured in an egress P2MP tunnel leaf range.Example: -count 3egress_ip_addr 5.5.5.5egress_ip_addr_step 1.0.0.0egress_leaf_range_count 3egress_leaf_range_step 0.1.0.0egress_leaf_ip_count 15Configuration Result:Egress1Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 5.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 5.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 5.7.5.5Leaf Count 15Egress 2Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 6.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 6.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 6.7.5.5Leaf Count 15Egress 3Tunnel Leaf Range 1Leaf Start Ip Address 7.5.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 2Leaf Start Ip Address 7.6.5.5Leaf Count 15Tunnel Leaf Range 3Leaf Start Ip Address 7.7.5.5Leaf Count 15(DEFAULT = N/A)Dependencies: N/A.

The following format must be used for IP type: ip,,ip = the 'ip' keywordipv4_address -- an IPv4 addressprefix -- the prefix length for the ip address (range 1-32)'l' - corresponding L bit in the packet will be set's' - corresponding L bit in the packet will not be setFor 'as' type the accepted format is as,, as -- 'as' keyword - number of the AS'l' - corresponding L bit in the packet will be set's' - corresponding L bit in the packet will not be setIn this way one ERO/SERO object is configured on all the Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects. You can configure multiple ERO/SERO objects on all the Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects by separating the format mentioned above with the ":" character.Example: "ip,1.0.1.0/32,s:ip,0.0.1.0/32,l"To configure a separate ERO/SERO object list on each Tunnel Head To Leaf you can pass this parameter on as a list.Example: count 2 h2l_info_tunnel_leaf_prefix_length [list 16 24]h2l_info_ero_sero_list [list ip,1.0.1.0/32,s:as,13,l ip,15.15.15.15/24,s:as,14,s] This will configure two P2MP tunnels. Each tunnel will have two Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects. The first Head To Leaf Info object will have two ERO/SERO objects (ip 1010 and as 13), the second will also have two ERO/SERO objects (ip 15.15.15.15 and as 14).

DEFAULT

 None

h2l_info_ero_sero_list

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.This parameter configures a list of ero/sero objects on a Tunnel Head To Leaf Information object. ERO/SERO objects can be configured as either IP or AS. The following format must be used for IP type: ip,,ip = the 'ip' keywordipv4_address -- an IPv4 addressprefix -- the prefix length for the ip address (range 1-32)'l' - corresponding L bit in the packet will be set's' - corresponding L bit in the packet will not be setFor 'as' type the accepted format is as,, as -- 'as' keyword - number of the AS'l' - corresponding L bit in the packet will be set's' - corresponding L bit in the packet will not be setIn this way one ERO/SERO object is configured on all the Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects. You can configure multiple ERO/SERO objects on all the Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects by separating the format mentioned above with the ":" character.Example: "ip,1.0.1.0/32,s:ip,0.0.1.0/32,l"To configure a separate ERO/SERO object list on each Tunnel Head To Leaf you can pass this parameter on as a list.Example: count 2 h2l_info_tunnel_leaf_prefix_length [list 16 24]h2l_info_ero_sero_list [list ip,1.0.1.0/32,s:as,13,l ip,15.15.15.15/24,s:as,14,s] This will configure two P2MP tunnels. Each tunnel will have two Tunnel Head To Leaf Info objects. The first Head To Leaf Info object will have two ERO/SERO objects (ip 1010 and as 13), the second will also have two ERO/SERO objects (ip 15.15.15.15 and as 14).

 None
